1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper primarily focuses on security and privacy protocols for wireless mesh networks, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the design of a communication protocol for wireless mesh networks, which is a subfield of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a protocol that is efficient in terms of storage and communication overhead, which is related to data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the need for robust and reliable communication protocols to minimize end-to-end latency and packet drops, which is related to information theory. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a protocol for wireless mesh networks, which involves software design and implementation, falling under the scope of software engineering.
